{"id":202493,"date":"2023-09-28T16:47:42","date_gmt":"2023-09-28T11:17:42","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/?p=202493"},"modified":"2023-09-28T17:56:30","modified_gmt":"2023-09-28T12:26:30","slug":"piyush-pandey","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/piyush-pandey\/","title":{"rendered":"Piyush Pandey Wiki, Age, Wife, Family, Biography &amp; More"},"content":{"rendered":"<p><a href=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/09\/Piyush-Pandey.jpg\"><img decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter wp-image-202693 \" src=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/09\/Piyush-Pandey.jpg\" alt=\"Piyush Pandey\" width=\"457\" height=\"556\" srcset=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/09\/Piyush-Pandey.jpg 600w, https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/09\/Piyush-Pandey-247x300.jpg 247w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 457px) 100vw, 457px\" \/><\/a><\/p>\n<p>Piyush Pandey is an Indian advertising professional and author. He is the Chief Creative Officer Worldwide and Executive Chairman of India of Ogilvy (agency). In 2016, he was honoured with the Padma Shri Award. He is considered the &#8216;Adman of India.&#8217; <span class=\"footnote_referrer relative\"><a role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"  on=\"tap:footnote_references_container_202493_1.toggleClass(class=collapsed, force=false),footnotes_container_button_plus_202493_1.toggleClass(class=collapsed, force=true),footnotes_container_button_minus_202493_1.toggleClass(class=collapsed, force=false)\"><sup id=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip_202493_1_1\" class=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip_text\">[1]<\/sup><\/a><span id=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip_text_202493_1_1\" class=\"footnote_tooltip position\" ><a href=\"https:\/\/www.forbesindia.com\/amp\/article\/storyboard18\/piyush-pandey-and-ogilvy-a-look-back-at-indian-advertisings-greatest-innings\/88565\/1\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow\">Forbes<\/a><\/span><\/span><\/p>\n<div id=\"ez-toc-container\" class=\"ez-toc-v2_0_62 counter-hierarchy ez-toc-counter ez-toc-custom ez-toc-container-direction\">\n<p class=\"ez-toc-title\">Contents<\/p>\n<label for=\"ez-toc-cssicon-toggle-item-65bce280bd6ba\" class=\"ez-toc-cssicon-toggle-label\"><span class=\"\"><span class=\"eztoc-hide\" style=\"display:none;\">Toggle<\/span><span class=\"ez-toc-icon-toggle-span\"><svg style=\"fill: #000000;color:#000000\" xmlns=\"http:\/\/www.w3.org\/2000\/svg\" class=\"list-377408\" width=\"20px\" height=\"20px\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"none\"><path d=\"M6 6H4v2h2V6zm14 0H8v2h12V6zM4 11h2v2H4v-2zm16 0H8v2h12v-2zM4 16h2v2H4v-2zm16 0H8v2h12v-2z\" fill=\"currentColor\"><\/path><\/svg><svg style=\"fill: #000000;color:#000000\" class=\"arrow-unsorted-368013\" xmlns=\"http:\/\/www.w3.org\/2000\/svg\" width=\"10px\" height=\"10px\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" version=\"1.2\" baseProfile=\"tiny\"><path d=\"M18.2 9.3l-6.2-6.3-6.2 6.3c-.2.2-.3.4-.3.7s.1.5.3.7c.2.2.4.3.7.3h11c.3 0 .5-.1.7-.3.2-.2.3-.5.3-.7s-.1-.5-.3-.7zM5.8 14.7l6.2 6.3 6.2-6.3c.2-.2.3-.5.3-.7s-.1-.5-.3-.7c-.2-.2-.4-.3-.7-.3h-11c-.3 0-.5.1-.7.3-.2.2-.3.5-.3.7s.1.5.3.7z\"\/><\/svg><\/span><\/span><\/label><input type=\"checkbox\"  id=\"ez-toc-cssicon-toggle-item-65bce280bd6ba\"  aria-label=\"Toggle\" \/><nav><ul class='ez-toc-list ez-toc-list-level-1 ' ><li class='ez-toc-page-1 ez-toc-heading-level-2'><a class=\"ez-toc-link ez-toc-heading-1\" href=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/piyush-pandey\/#WikiBiography\" title=\"Wiki\/Biography\">Wiki\/Biography<\/a><\/li><li class='ez-toc-page-1 ez-toc-heading-level-2'><a class=\"ez-toc-link ez-toc-heading-2\" href=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/piyush-pandey\/#Physical_Appearance\" title=\"Physical Appearance\">Physical Appearance<\/a><\/li><li class='ez-toc-page-1 ez-toc-heading-level-2'><a class=\"ez-toc-link ez-toc-heading-3\" href=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/piyush-pandey\/#Family\" title=\"Family\">Family<\/a><ul class='ez-toc-list-level-3' ><li class='ez-toc-heading-level-3'><a class=\"ez-toc-link ez-toc-heading-4\" href=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/piyush-pandey\/#Parents_Siblings\" title=\"Parents &amp; Siblings\">Parents &amp; Siblings<\/a><\/li><li class='ez-toc-page-1 ez-toc-heading-level-3'><a class=\"ez-toc-link ez-toc-heading-5\" href=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/piyush-pandey\/#Wife_Children\" title=\"Wife &amp; Children\">Wife &amp; Children<\/a><\/li><\/ul><\/li><li class='ez-toc-page-1 ez-toc-heading-level-2'><a class=\"ez-toc-link ez-toc-heading-6\" href=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/piyush-pandey\/#Career\" title=\"Career\">Career<\/a><ul class='ez-toc-list-level-3' ><li class='ez-toc-heading-level-3'><a class=\"ez-toc-link ez-toc-heading-7\" href=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/piyush-pandey\/#Advertising_Professional_Ogilvy\" title=\"Advertising Professional (Ogilvy)\">Advertising Professional (Ogilvy)<\/a><\/li><li class='ez-toc-page-1 ez-toc-heading-level-3'><a class=\"ez-toc-link ez-toc-heading-8\" href=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/piyush-pandey\/#Author\" title=\"Author\">Author<\/a><\/li><li class='ez-toc-page-1 ez-toc-heading-level-3'><a class=\"ez-toc-link ez-toc-heading-9\" href=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/piyush-pandey\/#Actor\" title=\"Actor\">Actor<\/a><\/li><\/ul><\/li><li class='ez-toc-page-1 ez-toc-heading-level-2'><a class=\"ez-toc-link ez-toc-heading-10\" href=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/piyush-pandey\/#Awards_Honours_Achievements\" title=\"Awards, Honours, Achievements\">Awards, Honours, Achievements<\/a><\/li><li class='ez-toc-page-1 ez-toc-heading-level-2'><a class=\"ez-toc-link ez-toc-heading-11\" href=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/piyush-pandey\/#FactsTrivia\" title=\"Facts\/Trivia\">Facts\/Trivia<\/a><\/li><\/ul><\/nav><\/div>\n<h2><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"WikiBiography\"><\/span>Wiki\/Biography<span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h2>\n<p>Piyush Pandey was born on Saturday, 9 April 1955 (<strong>age 68 years; as of 2023<\/strong>) in Jaipur, Rajasthan, India. His zodiac sign is Aries. He attended St. Xavier&#8217;s School in Jaipur. He holds an MA degree in History from St Stephen&#8217;s College, University of Delhi. <span class=\"footnote_referrer relative\"><a role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"  on=\"tap:footnote_references_container_202493_1.toggleClass(class=collapsed, force=false),footnotes_container_button_plus_202493_1.toggleClass(class=collapsed, force=true),footnotes_container_button_minus_202493_1.toggleClass(class=collapsed, force=false)\"><sup id=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip_202493_1_2\" class=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip_text\">[2]<\/sup><\/a><span id=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip_text_202493_1_2\" class=\"footnote_tooltip position\" ><a href=\"https:\/\/economictimes.indiatimes.com\/five-life-lessons-from-piyush-pandey-executive-chairman-at-ogilvy-mather-india\/articleshow\/34103654.cms?from=mdr\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow\">The Economic Times<\/a><\/span><\/span> He played cricket in the Ranji Trophy for the Rajasthan state team.<\/p>\n<div id=\"attachment_202704\" style=\"width: 640px\" class=\"wp-caption alignnone\"><a href=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/09\/A-young-age-photo-of-Piyush-Pandey-left-and-Prasoon-Pandey-right.jpeg\"><img decoding=\"async\" aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-202704\" class=\" wp-image-202704\" src=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/09\/A-young-age-photo-of-Piyush-Pandey-left-and-Prasoon-Pandey-right.jpeg\" alt=\"A young age photo of Piyush Pandey (left) and Prasoon Pandey (right)\" width=\"630\" height=\"356\" srcset=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/09\/A-young-age-photo-of-Piyush-Pandey-left-and-Prasoon-Pandey-right.jpeg 800w, https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/09\/A-young-age-photo-of-Piyush-Pandey-left-and-Prasoon-Pandey-right-300x170.jpeg 300w, https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/09\/A-young-age-photo-of-Piyush-Pandey-left-and-Prasoon-Pandey-right-768x434.jpeg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 630px) 100vw, 630px\" \/><\/a><p id=\"caption-attachment-202704\" class=\"wp-caption-text\">A young-age photo of Piyush Pandey (left) and Prasoon Pandey (right)<\/p><\/div>\n<h2><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"Physical_Appearance\"><\/span>Physical Appearance<span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h2>\n<p><strong>Height (approx.):<\/strong> 5&#8242; 9&#8243;<\/p>\n<p><strong>Hair Colour: <\/strong>Salt &amp; Pepper<\/p>\n<p><strong>Eye Colour: <\/strong>Black<\/p>\n<p><a href=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/09\/Piyush-Pandey-image.jpg\"><img decoding=\"async\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-202722\" src=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/09\/Piyush-Pandey-image.jpg\" alt=\"Piyush Pandey\" width=\"347\" height=\"800\" srcset=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/09\/Piyush-Pandey-image.jpg 347w, https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/09\/Piyush-Pandey-image-130x300.jpg 130w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 347px) 100vw, 347px\" \/><\/a><\/p>\n<h2><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"Family\"><\/span>Family<span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h2>\n<h3><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"Parents_Siblings\"><\/span><strong>Parents &amp; Siblings<\/strong><span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h3>\n<p>His father worked at a cooperative bank in Rajasthan, and his mother, Bhagwati Pandey, died in December 2010. <span class=\"footnote_referrer relative\"><a role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"  on=\"tap:footnote_references_container_202493_1.toggleClass(class=collapsed, force=false),footnotes_container_button_plus_202493_1.toggleClass(class=collapsed, force=true),footnotes_container_button_minus_202493_1.toggleClass(class=collapsed, force=false)\"><sup id=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip_202493_1_3\" class=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip_text\">[3]<\/sup><\/a><span id=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip_text_202493_1_3\" class=\"footnote_tooltip position\" ><a href=\"https:\/\/www.facebook.com\/photo.php?fbid=1602274543315664&amp;set=pb.100005994008545.-2207520000&amp;type=3\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow\">Facebook &#8211; Ila Arun<\/a><\/span><\/span> He has seven sisters including Rama Pandey, Tripati Pandey, and Ila Arun, and a younger brother named Prasoon Pandey, a well-known director of ad films. His sister, Ila Arun (elder), is a famous Indian singer and actress.<\/p>\n<div id=\"attachment_202713\" style=\"width: 578px\" class=\"wp-caption alignnone\"><a href=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/09\/Piyush-Pandeys-sister-Ila-Arun-and-mother.jpg\"><img decoding=\"async\" aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-202713\" class=\" wp-image-202713\" src=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/09\/Piyush-Pandeys-sister-Ila-Arun-and-mother.jpg\" alt=\"Piyush Pandey's sister, Ila Arun, and mother\" width=\"568\" height=\"443\" srcset=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/09\/Piyush-Pandeys-sister-Ila-Arun-and-mother.jpg 769w, https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/09\/Piyush-Pandeys-sister-Ila-Arun-and-mother-300x234.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 568px) 100vw, 568px\" \/><\/a><p id=\"caption-attachment-202713\" class=\"wp-caption-text\">Piyush Pandey&#8217;s sister, Ila Arun, and mother<\/p><\/div>\n<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n<div id=\"attachment_202701\" style=\"width: 578px\" class=\"wp-caption alignnone\"><a href=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/09\/Piyush-Pandey-with-Prasoon-Pandey-and-Ila-Arun.jpg\"><img decoding=\"async\" aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-202701\" class=\" wp-image-202701\" src=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/09\/Piyush-Pandey-with-Prasoon-Pandey-and-Ila-Arun.jpg\" alt=\"Piyush Pandey with Prasoon Pandey and Ila Arun\" width=\"568\" height=\"430\" srcset=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/09\/Piyush-Pandey-with-Prasoon-Pandey-and-Ila-Arun.jpg 793w, https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/09\/Piyush-Pandey-with-Prasoon-Pandey-and-Ila-Arun-300x227.jpg 300w, https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/09\/Piyush-Pandey-with-Prasoon-Pandey-and-Ila-Arun-768x581.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 568px) 100vw, 568px\" \/><\/a><p id=\"caption-attachment-202701\" class=\"wp-caption-text\">Piyush Pandey with Prasoon Pandey and Ila Arun<\/p><\/div>\n<h3><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"Wife_Children\"><\/span><strong>Wife &amp; Children<\/strong><span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h3>\n<p>In December 2000, he got married to Nita Joshi, his former colleague at Ogilvy &amp; Mather. Before getting married to each other, they were both previously married. He even attended Nita Joshi&#8217;s first marriage. <span class=\"footnote_referrer relative\"><a role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"  on=\"tap:footnote_references_container_202493_1.toggleClass(class=collapsed, force=false),footnotes_container_button_plus_202493_1.toggleClass(class=collapsed, force=true),footnotes_container_button_minus_202493_1.toggleClass(class=collapsed, force=false)\"><sup id=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip_202493_1_4\" class=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip_text\">[4]<\/sup><\/a><span id=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip_text_202493_1_4\" class=\"footnote_tooltip position\" ><a href=\"https:\/\/www.telegraphindia.com\/7-days\/i-was-born-in-a-creative-factory\/cid\/1313718\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow\">The Telegraph<\/a><\/span><\/span><\/p>\n<div id=\"attachment_202730\" style=\"width: 426px\" class=\"wp-caption alignnone\"><a href=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/09\/Piyush-Pandey-with-Nita-Pandey.jpeg\"><img decoding=\"async\" aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-202730\" class=\" wp-image-202730\" src=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/09\/Piyush-Pandey-with-Nita-Pandey.jpeg\" alt=\"Piyush Pandey with Nita Pandey\" width=\"416\" height=\"433\" srcset=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/09\/Piyush-Pandey-with-Nita-Pandey.jpeg 600w, https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/09\/Piyush-Pandey-with-Nita-Pandey-288x300.jpeg 288w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 416px) 100vw, 416px\" \/><\/a><p id=\"caption-attachment-202730\" class=\"wp-caption-text\">Piyush Pandey with Nita Pandey<\/p><\/div>\n<h2><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"Career\"><\/span>Career<span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h2>\n<p>Before getting into advertising, he also worked as a tea taster.<\/p>\n<h3><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"Advertising_Professional_Ogilvy\"><\/span><strong>Advertising Professional (Ogilvy)<\/strong><span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h3>\n<p>In 1982, he joined Ogilvy, a British advertising and marketing agency, as a client-servicing executive in India. His career in advertising began with a Sunlight Detergent print ad as it was the first ad written by him. For the 1988 National Integration campaign, he wrote the patriotic song &#8216;Mile Sur Mera Tumhara.&#8217; In 1989, he joined the creative department, where he designed many popular ad campaigns in India including a Pulse Polio ad campaign with the slogan &#8216;Do Boond Zindagi Ke&#8217; with <a href=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/amitabh-bachchan\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Amitabh Bachchan<\/a>, Fevicol ad campaigns, Fevikwik advertisements with the slogan &#8216;Todo Nahin, Jodo,&#8217; Ponds Ad (2010) with the popular slogan &#8216;Googly Woogly Woosh,&#8217; Cadbury Dairy Milk ad campaigns with the slogan &#8216;Kuch Khaas Hai,&#8217; Vodafone ad campaigns with Pug, ZooZoos, and Asian Paints advertisements with the slogan &#8216;Har Ghar Kuch Kehta Hai.&#8217;<\/p>\n<div class=\"flex-video flex-video-youtube\"><iframe title=\"Asian Paints - New TV Commercial- Har Ghar Kucch Kehta Hai-60sec\" width=\"1060\" height=\"795\" src=\"https:\/\/www.youtube.com\/embed\/b_u5C749aKQ?feature=oembed\" frameborder=\"0\" allow=\"accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture; web-share\" allowfullscreen><\/iframe><\/div>\n<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n<p>In 1992, he was promoted to creative director and later to national creative director. In 1994, he became its board member. Under his leadership, Ogilvy India held the top spot for 12 consecutive years in the Agency Reckoner, an independent marketing and advertising survey by The Economic Times and Brand Equity. In 2004, he was appointed as the Executive Chairman India &amp; South Asia for Ogilvy. Over his 40-year career at Ogilvy &amp; Mather, the agency became the largest advertising agency in India. In September 2006, Piyush Pandey was nominated to the Ogilvy Worldwide board. He also mentors creative executives from across the globe at the Berlin School of Creative Leadership. For the 2014 BJP election campaign, he and his team came up with the popular slogan &#8216;Abki Baar Modi Sarkar&#8217; and &#8216;Achche Din Aane Wale Hain.&#8217;<\/p>\n<div class=\"flex-video flex-video-youtube\"><iframe title=\"No Corruption, No Bhrashtachar - Isliye Abki Baar Modi Sarkaar\" width=\"1060\" height=\"795\" src=\"https:\/\/www.youtube.com\/embed\/pO03KAYlxd0?feature=oembed\" frameborder=\"0\" allow=\"accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture; web-share\" allowfullscreen><\/iframe><\/div>\n<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n<p>In 2019, he was appointed as Chief Creative Officer Worldwide of Ogilvy. In September 2023, he was announced to take on a larger advisory and leadership role at Ogilvy India, starting from 1 January 2024. <span class=\"footnote_referrer relative\"><a role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"  on=\"tap:footnote_references_container_202493_1.toggleClass(class=collapsed, force=false),footnotes_container_button_plus_202493_1.toggleClass(class=collapsed, force=true),footnotes_container_button_minus_202493_1.toggleClass(class=collapsed, force=false)\"><sup id=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip_202493_1_5\" class=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip_text\">[5]<\/sup><\/a><span id=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip_text_202493_1_5\" class=\"footnote_tooltip position\" ><a href=\"https:\/\/www.thehindubusinessline.com\/companies\/piyush-pandey-steps-down-as-ogilvy-india-chief\/article67353015.ece\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow\">The Hindu<\/a><\/span><\/span><\/p>\n<h3><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"Author\"><\/span><strong>Author<\/strong><span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h3>\n<p>In 2015, he published his first book &#8216;Pandeymonium: Piyush Pandey On Advertising.&#8217;<\/p>\n<div id=\"attachment_202744\" style=\"width: 400px\" class=\"wp-caption alignnone\"><a href=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/09\/Poster-of-the-2015-book-Pandeymonium-Piyush-Pandey-On-Advertising.jpeg\"><img decoding=\"async\" aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-202744\" class=\" wp-image-202744\" src=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/09\/Poster-of-the-2015-book-Pandeymonium-Piyush-Pandey-On-Advertising.jpeg\" alt=\"Poster of the 2015 book 'Pandeymonium - Piyush Pandey On Advertising'\" width=\"390\" height=\"627\" srcset=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/09\/Poster-of-the-2015-book-Pandeymonium-Piyush-Pandey-On-Advertising.jpeg 498w, https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/09\/Poster-of-the-2015-book-Pandeymonium-Piyush-Pandey-On-Advertising-187x300.jpeg 187w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 390px) 100vw, 390px\" \/><\/a><p id=\"caption-attachment-202744\" class=\"wp-caption-text\">Poster of the 2015 book &#8216;Pandeymonium &#8211; Piyush Pandey On Advertising&#8217;<\/p><\/div>\n<p>In 2022, he launched another book which was titled &#8216;Open House with Piyush Pandey&#8217; in which he wrote about his work, thoughts, and experiences. He also answered many questions that people asked him regarding advertising over the past decades.<\/p>\n<h3><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"Actor\"><\/span><strong>Actor<\/strong><span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h3>\n<p>In 1999, he, along with his brother Prasoon Pandey, wrote the story of the Hindi film &#8216;Bhopal Express.&#8217; In 2013, he played the role of \u00a0Cabinet Secretary of India in the Hindi political\u00a0action thriller film &#8216;Madras Cafe.&#8217;<\/p>\n<div id=\"attachment_202748\" style=\"width: 810px\" class=\"wp-caption alignnone\"><a href=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/09\/Piyush-Pandey-in-a-still-from-the-2013-Hindi-film-Madras-Cafe.jpg\"><img decoding=\"async\" aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-202748\" class=\"size-full wp-image-202748\" src=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/09\/Piyush-Pandey-in-a-still-from-the-2013-Hindi-film-Madras-Cafe.jpg\" alt=\"Piyush Pandey in a still from the 2013 Hindi film 'Madras Cafe'\" width=\"800\" height=\"327\" srcset=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/09\/Piyush-Pandey-in-a-still-from-the-2013-Hindi-film-Madras-Cafe.jpg 800w, https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/09\/Piyush-Pandey-in-a-still-from-the-2013-Hindi-film-Madras-Cafe-300x123.jpg 300w, https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/09\/Piyush-Pandey-in-a-still-from-the-2013-Hindi-film-Madras-Cafe-768x314.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px\" \/><\/a><p id=\"caption-attachment-202748\" class=\"wp-caption-text\">Piyush Pandey in a still from the 2013 Hindi film &#8216;Madras Cafe&#8217;<\/p><\/div>\n<h2><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"Awards_Honours_Achievements\"><\/span>Awards, Honours, Achievements<span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h2>\n<ul>\n<li>The Economic Times named him the most influential man in Indian advertising for eight consecutive years.<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<ul>\n<li>The Ad Club of Mumbai voted his commercial for Fevikwik the commercial of the century and his work for Cadbury the campaign of the century in 2000.<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<ul>\n<li>Voted Asia&#8217;s Creative Person of the Year at the Media Asia Award in 2002<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<ul>\n<li>The only Indian to win double gold at Cannes, which he received for his Cancer Patients Association anti-smoking campaign<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<ul>\n<li>Received a triple grand prize at the London International Awards<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<ul>\n<li>Received India&#8217;s first Silver Pencil at The One Show Award in 2002<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<ul>\n<li>Invited as a jury member at the Clio Awards in 2000<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<ul>\n<li>First jury President from Asia for outdoor and press and film at the Cannes Lions International Advertising Festival 2004<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<ul>\n<li>Invited to be a judge on the Asia Pacific Advertising Festival Awards 2007<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<ul>\n<li>Honoured with a lifetime achievement award from the Advertising Agencies Association of India in 2010<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<ul>\n<li>Earned Clio Lifetime Achievement Award in 2012<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<ul>\n<li>Honoured with the Padma Shri Award in 2016<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<ul>\n<li>He and his brother Prasoon Pandey won the Lions Lifetime Achievement Award of St. Mark at the Cannes Advertising Festival in France in June 2018.\n<p><div id=\"attachment_202755\" style=\"width: 547px\" class=\"wp-caption alignnone\"><a href=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/09\/Piyush-Pandey-with-Prasoon-Pandey-after-winning-the-Lions-Lifetime-Achievement-Award-of-St.-Mark-in-2018.jpg\"><img decoding=\"async\" aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-202755\" class=\" wp-image-202755\" src=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/09\/Piyush-Pandey-with-Prasoon-Pandey-after-winning-the-Lions-Lifetime-Achievement-Award-of-St.-Mark-in-2018.jpg\" alt=\"Piyush Pandey with Prasoon Pandey after winning the Lions Lifetime Achievement Award of St. Mark in 2018\" width=\"537\" height=\"427\" srcset=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/09\/Piyush-Pandey-with-Prasoon-Pandey-after-winning-the-Lions-Lifetime-Achievement-Award-of-St.-Mark-in-2018.jpg 755w, https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/09\/Piyush-Pandey-with-Prasoon-Pandey-after-winning-the-Lions-Lifetime-Achievement-Award-of-St.-Mark-in-2018-300x238.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 537px) 100vw, 537px\" \/><\/a><p id=\"caption-attachment-202755\" class=\"wp-caption-text\">Piyush Pandey with Prasoon Pandey after winning the Lions Lifetime Achievement Award of St. Mark in 2018<\/p><\/div><\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<h2><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"FactsTrivia\"><\/span>Facts\/Trivia<span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h2>\n<ul>\n<li>Piyush Pandey likes to collect Ganesha idols.\n<p><div id=\"attachment_202796\" style=\"width: 618px\" class=\"wp-caption alignnone\"><a href=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/09\/Piyush-Pandey-with-his-collection-of-Ganesha-idols.jpg\"><img decoding=\"async\" aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-202796\" class=\" wp-image-202796\" src=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/09\/Piyush-Pandey-with-his-collection-of-Ganesha-idols.jpg\" alt=\"Piyush Pandey with his collection of Ganesha idols\" width=\"608\" height=\"341\" srcset=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/09\/Piyush-Pandey-with-his-collection-of-Ganesha-idols.jpg 800w, https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/09\/Piyush-Pandey-with-his-collection-of-Ganesha-idols-300x168.jpg 300w, https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/09\/Piyush-Pandey-with-his-collection-of-Ganesha-idols-768x431.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 608px) 100vw, 608px\" \/><\/a><p id=\"caption-attachment-202796\" class=\"wp-caption-text\">Piyush Pandey with his collection of Ganesha idols<\/p><\/div><\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<ul>\n<li>In 2016, he gave a TEDx speech about &#8216;How to narrate an unforgettable story.&#8217; In 2018, he gave another TEDx speech which was on the topic &#8216;Change and constant are like body and soul.&#8217;\n<p><div id=\"attachment_202759\" style=\"width: 737px\" class=\"wp-caption alignnone\"><a href=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/09\/Piyush-Pandey-during-his-TEDx-speech-in-2016.jpg\"><img decoding=\"async\" aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-202759\" class=\" wp-image-202759\" src=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/09\/Piyush-Pandey-during-his-TEDx-speech-in-2016.jpg\" alt=\"Piyush Pandey during his TEDx speech in 2016\" width=\"727\" height=\"369\" srcset=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/09\/Piyush-Pandey-during-his-TEDx-speech-in-2016.jpg 800w, https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/09\/Piyush-Pandey-during-his-TEDx-speech-in-2016-300x152.jpg 300w, https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/09\/Piyush-Pandey-during-his-TEDx-speech-in-2016-768x390.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 727px) 100vw, 727px\" \/><\/a><p id=\"caption-attachment-202759\" class=\"wp-caption-text\">Piyush Pandey during his TEDx speech in 2016<\/p><\/div><\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<ul>\n<li>In an interview, while talking about his annual ritual that he does on every New Year&#8217;s Eve, he said,<br \/>\n<blockquote><p>Every 31st December from 7 to 9, I shut myself off completely and ask what I had done through the year. And that decides whether I sleep well or not. It&#8217;s an exercise to determine whether I just travelled and did this and that or some actual work.&#8221;<\/p><\/blockquote>\n<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<div class=\"489bcfb86580b123547338c91db0eff2\" data-index=\"3\" style=\"float: none; margin:3px 0 3px 0; text-align:center;\">\n<ins class=\"adsbygoogle\"\r\n     style=\"display:block\"\r\n     data-ad-format=\"autorelaxed\"\r\n     data-ad-client=\"ca-pub-6769524711517462\"\r\n     data-ad-slot=\"2473600074\"><\/ins>\n<\/div>\n\n<div style=\"font-size: 0px; height: 0px; line-height: 0px; margin: 0; padding: 0; clear: both;\"><\/div><div class=\"speaker-mute footnotes_reference_container\"> <div class=\"footnote_container_prepare\"><p><span role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\" id=\"footnotes_container_label_expand_202493_1\" class=\"footnote_reference_container_label pointer\" on=\"tap:footnote_references_container_202493_1.toggleClass(class=collapsed),footnotes_container_button_plus_202493_1.toggleClass(class=collapsed),footnotes_container_button_minus_202493_1.toggleClass(class=collapsed)\">References<\/span><span role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\" id=\"footnotes_containe